<!channel> my OMSI work lately has had a lot to do with Core Animation and Auto Layout. While I'm out of town this week I'm going to work on slides about this, and after I get back I'd be happy to do a brown bag dev lunch talk about (a) how to use NSLayoutConstraints, (b) why they're better than springs & struts, and (c) what to do when you need more "manual" control of your views.
It would largely be a developer-centered talk, with lots of code examples. And the knowledge will be universal between Mac and iOS development.
<@U026PT0D7> You should make this talk open to the public. Pretty sure there're other people out there interested in this too.
Good idea! <@U026NB2U2> who do I talk to about Uncorked hosting this for the public?
